Cytonn Real Estate Management has started construction on its mixed-use development project along Kiambu Road valued at Sh12 billion. The property on 10 acres, dubbed The Ridge, will have 700 housing units on completion, comprised of one-, two- and three-bedroom apartments. The project will also put up three-bedroom houses with a servant quarters and penthouses that occupy the topmost floors.The Ridge is part of projects by Cytonn, largely targeting the middle class. Others include Amara Ridge in Karen, Alma in Ruaka, Taraji Height and Situ Village in Karen. &ldquo;Real Estate continues to offer the very best returns for both the investors and end users,&rdquo; Cytonn chief investment officer Elizabeth Nkukuu said at the ground breaking ceremony held yesterday.